cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.SC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new supercomputer topology and routing scheme. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the bandwidth utilization and routing of the proposed network. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possibility as the paper proposes a new hardware architecture for a supercomputer. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper discusses the fault-tolerance and deadlock-freedom properties of the proposed communication scheme. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is unlikely as the paper does not appear to involve symbolic computation.
